This paper describes a system for speech synthesis using neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The use of neural networks also suggests that the paper could fall under cs.SD (Sound), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these sub-categories are related to the use of neural networks in various applications. Finally, the paper could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as speech synthesis is a common application of AI.
